```javascript
{
  "identifiers": false,
  "ignore": null,
  "jsx": false,
  "reporter": "default",
  "suppress": 100,
  "threshold": 15
}
```

This JSON schema defines a structure for configuring the behavior of a JavaScript inspection tool. It includes various fields such as `identifiers`, `ignore`, `jsx`, `reporter`, `suppress`, and `threshold`. Each field has its own purpose and can be set based on specific requirements or conditions. The `idents` property indicates if the tool should limit its search to nodes with matching identifiers. The `ignore` field allows specifying regular expressions to match paths to ignore. The `jsx` field determines whether to process JSX files. The `reporter` field specifies the name of the reporter to use. The `suppress` field sets the number of lines at which diffs should be suppressed. Finally, the `threshold` field specifies the minimum subset of nodes to analyze before reporting any changes.